nism in art. Beautifully illustrated with more than 140 paintings and drawings, this book serves as an essential reference on Seurat.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aNeo-impressionism (Art). 0aVisual perception in art. 7aART / Individual Artists / Monographs.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030020835140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021282240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300212822423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300212822/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY